reviews.review_text:
Good show the europe 90 tour is kind of a bitter taste for all of us europeans who didn't go to see the dead with Jerry 

the tour was so good SO SORRY TO MISSED IT

KEEP ON JAMMIN IN HEAVEN JERRY

This is just so good .......... From a sbd (silent but deadly)fan to Mr. Taper:

This is just so good - more than enough to re-ignite the old sbd/aud/matrix debate.

Everything is clear as a bell, but with that added audience factor.

To messrs Chappy/Tobin/Seamons - no work for you here (though I am a 'sometimes' fan) - normally you add a bit of aud to the sbd for atmosphere or a bit of sbd to the aud for clarity (feel free to correct me if you like) but both are already here in what seems the perfect ratio. (Again) Feel free to prove me wrong.

I'll avoid the temptation of giving it 5 stars just 'cos I was there and stick with the current 4 (in all honesty they were way past their best, Jerry's voice was shot though Bob does his best to compensate and there is the added Hornsby factor - but this is no "Live/Dead").

That said, a good show very well recorded. I'll have to check out some more of your tapes.

U sure it ain't a soundboard?

"Doreen and Pat" phone call? Thanks for the recommend 844-1009; What is the "Doreen and Pat" phone call?  Sounded a little PFloyd-ish live & my tapes came out pretty good.  The sound at Wembley was outstanding (thanks Dan!).
